# Appointment Booking System

This project consists of three main components: a backend server, a frontend application, and an embeddable booking widget plugin.

## Backend

The backend is built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB, providing the core booking functionality and data management.

### Features
- RESTful API endpoints for booking management
- MongoDB integration for data persistence
- Available time slots generation
- Booking validation and management

### Setup and Running
1. Navigate to the backend directory:
   ```bash
   cd backend
   ```
2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```
3. Create a `.env` file with the following variables:
   ```
   PORT=5000
   MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
   ```
4. Run the server:
   - Development mode: `npm run dev`
   - Production mode: `npm start`

The server will start on port 5000 by default.

## Frontend

The frontend is a React application that provides an admin interface for managing bookings.

### Features
- Dashboard to view all bookings
- Calendar view of appointments
- Booking management (view, edit, cancel)
- Real-time updates

### Setup and Running
1. Navigate to the frontend directory:
   ```bash
   cd frontend
   ```
2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```
3. Start the development server:
   ```bash
   npm start
   ```

The frontend will run on port 3000 by default.

## Booking Widget Plugin

A standalone JavaScript widget that can be embedded into any website to provide booking functionality.

### Features
- User-friendly booking interface
- Dynamic time slot selection
- Form validation
- Responsive design

### Integration
Add the following script tag to your HTML:
<!-- <script src="https://your-cdn.com/booking-widget.js"></script> -->
